faqs:
  - q: "What is Wrestling City Tactics?"
    a: "Wrestling City Tactics is a turn-based tactics RPG from BuilderFox. Matches play out on a grid, turn by turn, and every result feeds a city-wide wrestling storyline — position wins the match, drama wins the city."
  - q: "What kind of game is it?"
    a: "Turn-based tactics with RPG depth: grid-based combat, a roster of original wrestling personas to scout and develop, stables and factions to build, and kayfabe storylines that react to every win, loss, and betrayal."
  - q: "Is there a release date?"
    a: "Not yet. The game is in production, and we don't announce dates we can't keep — it ships when it's sharp. Join the notify list (email aaron@builderfox.com) and you'll hear the bell first."
  - q: "Who is making Wrestling City Tactics?"
    a: "BuilderFox — a creative agency that builds and publishes digital games, founded by Aaron. Wrestling City Tactics is our first title: original systems, original art, original stories."
  - q: "Are the wrestlers real people?"
    a: "No. Every wrestler in the city is an original persona created for the game — no real-world likenesses, no licensed legends, no borrowed faces. The gimmicks are ours, and the lawyers sleep fine."
